1. c4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 a6 5. d4 e6 6. b3 Bb4 7. Bd2 Nbd7 8. Bd3 dxc4 {An interesting attempt.} 9. bxc4 (9. Bxc4 {In the Accelerated Meran, this is almost always the worst recapture.} O-O 10. O-O {This is likely to transpose to the previous chapter.} b5 11. Be2 Bd6 $5 {Not necessary, but the simplest.} 12. e4 e5 {We have transposed to O-O O-O Bd6 e4 dxc4} 13. Bc4 {e5 , analyzed here .}) 9... e5 {This is the point of Lokander's novelty. By making use of some small tactical ideas, we can execute the ... e5 -break in the fastest way possible!} 10. Qc2 {This is a very natural square for the queen in the Meran. Here there are some differences to 10. Qb1 - the main one being that the bishop on b4 isn't hanging.} Qe7 {This is highly important. Were we to play ... Bd6 immediately, the queen would simply be better on c2 than on d1 . But now we see another difference with the queen moves: the b4 -bishop isn't hanging, meaning we can safely recapture on e5 .} 11. Be2 {Highlighting the downside for White: they have to lose a tempo as we were again threatening ... e4 , winning a piece. That is the reason the engines are much more in favour of Qb1 instead of Qc2 .} O-O 12. O-O Re8 {The most flexible move. We shouldn't rush with ... Bd6 , as we want to keep the option of ... Bxc3 in some moments.} (12... e4 $2 {It's important to understand that this doesn't work.} 13. Nxe4 $1 Nxe4 14. Bxb4 Qxb4 15. Qxe4) 13. c5 {This is the other critical way of playing. White prevents ... Bd6 and fixes our weakness on b7 . Now we are strategically worse in the long run, so we must act quickly before White can consolidate.} exd4 {Opening up the e-file, making good use of our Re8 -tempo.} 14. exd4 Bxc3 {This is the point. White can't recapture with the bishop, as e2 is hanging.} 15. Qxc3 Ne4 (15... Qxe2 $4 16. Rfe1 Qb5 17. Rxe8+ Nxe8 18. a4 {traps the queen!} Qe2 19. Re1 {White is winning.}) 16. Qb2 {Any other square would lead to the same.} Nxd2 17. Qxd2 Nf8 {The last key move. We want our knight on f8 to support ... Be6 next. In general, the d4 -pawn is as weak as our b7 -pawn and our pieces are no worse than White's.} *

