1. c4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 a6 5. d4 e6 6. b3 Bb4 7. Bd2 Nbd7 8. Bd3 dxc4 {An interesting attempt.} 9. bxc4 (9. Bxc4 {In the Accelerated Meran, this is almost always the worst recapture.} O-O 10. O-O {This is likely to transpose to the previous chapter.} b5 11. Be2 Bd6 $5 {Not necessary, but the simplest.} 12. e4 e5 {We have transposed to O-O O-O Bd6 e4 dxc4} 13. Bc4 {e5 , analyzed here .}) 9... e5 {This is the point of Lokander's novelty. By making use of some small tactical ideas, we can execute the ... e5 -break in the fastest way possible!} 10. Qb1 {This is the favorite move of the engines, and from an objective point of view the most critical move.} (10. O-O $2 {It's worth pointing out that our last move actually created a threat!} Bxc3 11. Bxc3 e4 {Winning a piece.}) 10... Bd6 (10... Qe7 $2 {Would be the most natural move, but, unfortunately, it does not really work here.} 11. dxe5 $1 Ng4 12. O-O Ndxe5 13. Nxe5 Nxe5 14. Nd5 $1 {And Black collapses.}) 11. O-O O-O {This is the position that the engines are considering to be slightly better for White. However, when going a bit deeper it becomes clear that Black has plenty of counterplay, as well as the position being rather easy to play. Our idea is the same against almost anything: we want to play ... Re8 , ... h6 and ... Qe7 , followed by pushing ... e4} 12. a4 {Another strategic idea, trying to claim that our b7 -pawn is a weakness.} Re8 13. h3 h6 {The nice thing about this line is that we can play these moves against almost anything White does} 14. Rd1 {As White with 12. a4 has decided to no longer play on the kingside, this makes sense.} Qe7 15. Ne4 Nxe4 16. Bxe4 exd4 {Not necessary, but an interesting idea.} 17. Bh7+ {The bishop was hanging.} Kh8 18. exd4 c5 {The idea. Pushing ... c5 like this often makes sense as well. Should White play d5 , we get a nice square on e5 for our knight and White loses all potential in the center. The downside is that d5 becomes a protected passed pawn, but we have a fantastic blockading bishop on d6 . If White doesn't play d5 , we take on d4 and get access to the nice c5 -square.} *

