1. c4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 a6 5. d4 e6 {We have discussed all the previous moves in the 6. b3  Introduction .} 6. Qc2 {This was one of Gelfand's attempts in the match with Anand.} c5 {This is my recommendation, and in fact the only good move. It looks strange to lose a tempo, but the queen is not really better on c2 than on d1 .} (6... Nbd7 $6 7. b3 {This is the issue. Compared to 6.b3 we are not in time to provoke the bishop to d2 .} Bb4 (7... Bd6 {If we were to play a normal Meran setup like this, the move ... a6 would be a waste.}) 8. Bb2 Ne4 9. Bd3 {White is ready to castle next.}) 7. cxd5 {The critical move.} (7. a3 {Such moves are popular in practice, but do not really require a lot of theoretical knowledge to meet.} dxc4 8. dxc5 Bxc5 9. Bxc4 Nbd7 {Followed by ... O-O and ... b5 ... Bb7 is harmonious for Black.}) 7... exd5 8. Be2 (8. dxc5 Bxc5 {Solid for White but official theory suggests Black is doing well, which I agree with.}) 8... cxd4 {This is my recommendation, immediately forcing the issue in the center. It's not better than the alternatives, but I believe it's a bit simpler.} (8... Nc6 9. O-O Be6 {This is the big mainline.} 10. Rd1 cxd4 (10... Nb4 {Another sharp line, but I don't trust it too much. To me, it looks shaky for Black.}) 11. Nxd4 Nxd4 12. Rxd4 Bc5 13. Rd1 Qe7 14. Bf3 O-O 15. Nxd5 Nxd5 16. Bxd5 Bxd5 17. Rxd5 Rac8 {This has been the traditional mainline. Black is supposed to have enough compensation for a draw. It's obviously very solid, but slightly too sad for my taste.}) 9. Nxd4 (9. exd4 {Hardly an issue. In the symmetrical structure arising White has no real grounds to hope for an advantage.}) 9... Bd6 {This is one of the reasons I like to trade on d4 already on move 8 - now our bishop can immediately go to the most active diagonal.} 10. O-O (10. e4 {This is the sharpest try for White, but in practical play it's rather rare. It's something we should be aware of as Black though.}) 10... O-O {Followed by ... Nc6 . We usually get hanging pawns for which our piece play compensates.} *

