1. c4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 a6 5. d4 e6 6. Bd3 {This is the main move in the normal Meran, but in the Accelerated Meran it's actually a fair bit less popular.} dxc4 7. Bxc4 b5 {This is resembling a normal Meran a lot, but it's specifically this position that gives the name 'Accelerated' its meaning. It is accelerated for Black in the sense that by playing ... a6 instead of ... Nbd7 , we are actually able to push ... c5 one move earlier, as the b5 -pawn is already protected.} 8. Bd3 Bb7 ({A small move order subtlety.} 8... c5 9. a4 b4 10. Ne4 {is slightly annoying.}) 9. O-O (9. e4 c5 {Gives excellent counterplay. Again, it's an advantage not having had to play ... Nbd7 yet.}) 9... c5 {Gives good play against the center. It's important that we managed to play it before White got e4 in.} 10. a4 b4 {This is the difference. Now White can't play Ne4 , and we are more than fine.} *

