1. c4 c6 2. Nf3 d5 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 a6 5. d4 e6 6. Bd3 {This is the main move in the normal Meran, but in the Accelerated Meran it's actually a fair bit less popular.} dxc4 7. Bxc4 b5 {This is resembling a normal Meran a lot, but it's specifically this position that gives the name 'Accelerated' its meaning. It is accelerated for Black in the sense that by playing ... a6 instead of ... Nbd7 , we are actually able to push ... c5 one move earlier, as the b5 -pawn is already protected.} 8. Be2 {This modest looking move is actually the most dangerous one for Black. As we are going to play ... c5 anyway, the bishop is vulnerable on both d3 and b3 , therefore White tries to tuck it safely away on e2 .} c5 9. e4 {This is possible, but hardly scary.} cxd4 10. Qxd4 Be7 {Slightly unusual, but makes sense. We want to recapture with the bishop on d8 , as it can then proceed to b6 or a5 , both nice squares. The White e4 -pawns looks a little overextended here.} *

