White's best bet, at least initiating some trades.} Nb4 11. Nxb4 Bxb4+ 12. Nc3 Bf7 {Not necessary, but a nice move. After White has played e4 , we no longer play for a direct attack. Instead, we are switching to positional play, particularly making use of the d4 -square. Our pawn on e5 is isolated, but close to impossible for White to attack. It seems fairly balanced, but we definitely have easy play.} *

