.. e6 and ... c6 . This means that the g2 -bishop will be blunted basically forever. The downside for us is that it does take some time, and the knight is in itself not that great on b6 .} 4. b3 Bf5 5. Nh4 {Another version of this, but b3 is a bit slower than Nc3 or Nd2 , so we can safely continue in our preferred fashion.} (5. Ba3 c6 {This should be compared to a4 a5 b3 . Basically including a4  a5 is a bit better for White, so as long as we react in the same way here we are in good shape.}) 5... Bg4 {Basically, we just have an improved version of 4. Nc3 here, and as long as we know that line we should be fine here as well.} *

[Event "?"]
