.. e6 and ... c6 . This means that the g2 -bishop will be blunted basically forever. The downside for us is that it does take some time, and the knight is in itself not that great on b6 .} 4. Nc3 {This is the most critical move for White, although in practice it hasn't yet taken over. When I faced this line myself as White, I choose 4. Nc3 , and when I prepared to play it with Black, it was 4. Nc3 that was my main focus of attention. Indeed, the one classical game I tried the Nd7 - b6 line my opponent played 4. Nc3 . The point for White is rather specific - they anticipate us playing ... Bf5 next, and want to meet it with Nh4 . Surprisingly, the g2 -square is going to be needed for the knight rather than the bishop! Sounds strange, but it will all become clear once we look at the concrete lines.} Bf5 5. Nh4 {The most direct move, and the point of 4. Nc3 .} Bg4 {This is our concept. We don't want to allow White to take on f5 . It is my understanding that the idea of ... Bg4 is still an underestimated one. For instance, when I got to play it myself recently against the very strong GM Theodorou he was completely unaware what to do against it, and I myself when playing this line with White hadn't really taken ... Bg4 seriously, instead expecting to get the very pleasant positions after Nxf5 next. Generally, ... Bg4 to my taste is the perfect balance between being somewhat provocative while still sound.} 6. h3 {The main move, and the one Theodorou tried against me.} Bh5 7. Ng2 {This is White's point, and precisely the reason why 4. Nc3 had to be played instead of 4. Bg2 .} e6 {I played 7... Nf6 myself against Theodorou but analyzing the game afterwards I understood that this is a better move order. The main point is actually to keep the f-pawn flexible. In certain situations, we are happily playing ... f5 to further our grip of the center.} 8. Nf4 Bg6 9. Bg2 {Delaying the swap on g6 , hoping for ... Nf6 so that we no longer have our ... f5 -idea.} Bb4 {An important way to put pressure. I've said a few times that the knight on b6 is rather a bad piece, but if we are allowed to take on c3 things are completely different - then the knight would be our best piece on c4 !} *

