1. b3 d5 {There are other good moves against 1. b3 of course, but insofar as possible I like to keep the structures within Slav territory.} 2. Bb2 Bg4 ({A move I've dabbed with a fair amount myself throughout the years. It's slightly less solid than} 2... Bf5 {, but it's provocative in a nice way. We invite White to attack our bishop, but in doing so they would weaken their position. And should White choose to leave the bishop be on g4 , then it's simply well-placed there.}) 3. Nf3 {This is the lazy approach for White. They simply develop without bothering to look too carefully at what we are doing.} Nf6 {In my own practice I've often taken on f3 here, but nowadays, I think it's a bit simpler to simply keep developing.} 4. e3 {Another way to play. Against the ... Bf5 -setups this is even more innocent than g3 , but against ... Bg4 I would actually say e3 is the more ambitious setup. The reason is that White has an additional plan of hunting down our g4 -bishop here.} e6 5. h3 Bh5 {Actually, trading on f3 is always possible as well, and leads to positions similar to many from the Classical Slav. Still, it seems to me a bit more ambitious to try to keep the bishop.} 6. d3 {This looks like the trickiest move. White wants to play g4 , but it's a bit more flexible to start with d3 .} a5 {A concrete reaction. We immediately ask White some questions. Getting the pawn to a4 is a big nuisance for White.} 7. a3 {Far and away the most natural move for White.} a4 {This is our idea. It's not always a good idea, but here it works out well. We are simply fighting for the initiative already!} 8. b4 {The only move that makes strategic sense.} c5 {This is the point of our play. We trade a c-pawn for a b-pawn which is not normally great, but we gain a lot of time in the process. Pushing ... c5 also means that our knight gets a great square on c6 , and long-term we might be able to push ... e5 , gaining even more space.} 9. bxc5 Bxc5 10. Be2 Nc6 {I like Black. All our pieces are excellently placed, we have a space advantage and no real weaknesses.} *

