is a bit happy here.}) 12. Bc2 b6 13. a3 {This is a typical setup, preparing Qd3 to go for some attack. But we are way too solid for that to work.} Bb7 (13... Ba6 $5 {simply preventing Qd3 also makes sense.}) 14. Qd3 Ne7 {A key part of our defense. The knight goes to f5 , from where it will prevent any reasonable attacking attempts from White.} *

