1. c4 c6 2. e4 {The Panov. This one is slightly annoying. Not because it is in any way challenging theoretically, but because it leads to a bit more theory than I usually prefer.} d5 3. exd5 cxd5 4. d4 {This is now a real Panov.} Nf6 5. Nc3 Nc6 6. Bg5 {This is a sharp sideline. We basically only need to know one line here, but if we don't, then it can be really unpleasant.} Be6 {Looks very odd, but White is almost certainly going to take on f6 , and after we recapture with the e-pawn the bishop on e6 looks normal again.} 7. a3 {Looks funny but there is a concrete idea behind it. White prevents a later check on b4 .} (7. Bxf6 exf6 8. a3 {This is also a possible, albeit slightly strange move order. I still believe we should transpose, though.} g6 {transposing to the current line.}) 7... g6 {With the bishop on e6 we are not going to play ... e6 anymore, therefore fianchettoing the bishop is the logical way.} 8. Bxf6 {White actually have to go for this. Otherwise, the move Bg5 would simply be a waste.} exf6 9. cxd5 {Again, if White does nothing direct, and we get castled we would simply be better with the bishop pair.} Bxd5 10. Qe2+ {This is the specific position we really, really need to know.} Ne7 {The only move, but luckily equalizing confidently.} (10... Be7 $4 11. Qb5 $1 {Suddenly White wins a piece! This is a trick I have fallen for myself in blitz, so please be aware.}) 11. Nxd5 {White still has to act fast.} Qxd5 12. Qb5+ {An annoying check, as we don't have access to the f8 -square for our king yet.} Kd8 {It looks risky, but the queens are coming off the next move, so the king is entirely safe on d8 .} 13. Qxd5+ Nxd5 {It looks odd what we are doing, accepting both a doubled pawn and the king in the center. But in fact it is nothing to worry about. The d-pawn will never move, and we have a nice blockade on d6 which White will never, ever be able to break. Additionally, we have quick access to both the c- and e-files for our rooks. The opposite coloured bishops gives the position certain drawing tendencies, but that is really the only downside I can see.} *

