1. g4 {A horrendous move, weakening an entire complex of squares without getting anything in return.} d5 2. Bg2 Nc6 {A funny antidote, but obviously just one of many good options. The idea is to prevent d4 , and always meet c4 with …d4. Without any of these moves, White is struggling to generate counterplay, letting us take over the center with …e5 next.} *

