a piece, and for that reason we don't want to play ... Nc6 . But by playing ... Qc8 , we get ready to overprotect d5 with ... Rd8 , after which we are finally ready to play ... Nc6 . Meanwhile, it's not easy for White to do anything about it.} 10. Qe2 {The most common move. This is simply how White puts their pieces in this line.} Rd8 {Even creating a small threat of ... d4 - d3} 11. Rfd1 d4 {Now White gets misplaced.} 12. exd4 cxd4 13. Nb5 d3 {Another reason why the rook is useful on d8 !} 14. Qe3 Nc6 {The pawn on d3 is a great asset for us.} *

