1. c4 e6 2. g3 {Fianchettoing the bishop is arguably White's most critical way of playing. Very often, the game now transposes to a normal Catalan. Of course, that's outside the scope of our repertoire, but we never have to allow a real transposition.} d5 3. Bg2 dxc4 {I have chosen to always recommend the capture on c4 . This eliminates the risk of a real Catalan transposition, which is a big upside. The other way to avoid that is to play 3... d4 , but I feel that those positions are much trickier to handle for Black, and also leads to structures that we are a lot less familiar with.} 4. Qa4+ Qd7 {Very controversial! From thousands of games, this has only been played in a handful. I was unaware of the move until my good friend and teammate, the highly creative GM Mateusz Bartel, played it in an important game in the European Club Cup, winning in excellent style.} 5. Qxc4 c5 {This is the idea. The queen looks strange on d7 , but it gives us the possibility of playing ... Nc6 without every worrying about White capturing the c6 -knight. Now we want to play ... Nc6 , ... Nf6 , ... Be7 and ... O-O , but after that we have two ways of developing, depending on what White does: either ... b6  Bb7 , or, in case White tries to push d4 , to play ... e5 ourselves, preventing that.} 6. Nf3 Nc6 7. O-O Nf6 8. Rd1 {Another logical move, but likely to transpose elsewhere.} Be7 9. d4 cxd4 10. Nxd4 {This is a big mistake, but I believe it's not at all unlikely.} (10. e3 O-O 11. exd4 b6 {intending ... Bb7 looks solid enough.}) 10... e5 {Due to the pin, it looks like we are winning material, but actually White is the one winning material.} 11. Bxc6 bxc6 12. Qxc6 exd4 {The only move, but a very strong one. It turns out we get fantastic compensation for the exchange. This is definitely possible to miss as White.} 13. Qxa8 O-O 14. Qg2 {The only move, otherwise White is simply getting mated soon.} Bb7 15. f3 Bc5 {We are a significant amount of material down, but nevertheless close to winning. There will simply be too many attackers soon. Especially the e2 -pawn is very weak.} *

