1. c4 e6 2. g3 d5 3. Nf3 dxc4 4. Bg2 Nd7 {A good move order. Developing the queenside is much more important than the kingside, which can wait.} 5. Qa4 (5. Qc2 Nb6 {Important to hold onto the pawn whenever allowed.}) (5. Na3 Bxa3 {We always take this knight.}) 5... a6 6. Qxc4 b5 7. Qc2 Bb7 8. O-O Ngf6 9. Nc3 c5 10. a4 Bc6 {Important to never play ... b4 , as it gives up the c4 -square for no reason.} *

