1. Nf3 d5 2. e4 {Apparently this is known as the “Tennison” Gambit. It used to be popular in my youth, but that was in Bughouse rather than chess… Needless to say, there are many ways for Black to get an advantage.} dxe4 3. Ng5 e5 {As usual, I prefer not going for the most materialistic approach, but instead opting for maximum activity.} 4. d3 Be7 {Again not grabbing material, although this time it was very tempting as well.} 5. Nxe4 f5 {We have a considerable lead in development and more central control. I don’t think we can ask for more as Black on move 5!} *

