hallenging moves. I think a well-prepared White player is pretty likely to play this if faced with 2... b6 .} Ngf6 9. Nce5 O-O 10. d4 Nxe5 11. dxe5 Qd7 {An important intermediate move.} 12. Qf4 Nd5 13. Qg4 f5 {This is why we needed ... Qd7 . Now the e6 -pawn is safely defended.} 14. exf6 Nxf6 {Our structure is slightly worse, but we have excellent piece play to compensate for that.} *

