ite has a concrete idea.} 15. e5 {A typical tactic. Normally it would be winning for White, but we have a surprising resource.} Rad8 {Amazingly, it all holds together well for us.} 16. exf6 Nxf6 17. Qe2 Bxg2 18. Kxg2 {It looks like White survived with an extra piece, but now comes our point.} a6 {The knight is trapped! After winning back the piece, the game is just equal.} *

