23. Bh5 {Black to move. Can you find the strongest move in the position?} Nh4+ {Even stronger than the game continuation.} (23... Nf4+ {Not actually leading to an advantage, but a typical tactical idea towards White's king, especially with the two strong bishops on c7 and c8 .} 24. gxf4 Qxf4 25. Nf3 (25. Re3 {This is a crazy engine move that gives up an exchange, but everybody would prefer to be Black here.} Qh2+ 26. Kf1 Bf4 27. Qb3 {The only move!} Kh8 28. Ke2 Bxe3 29. Qxe3 Bxh3 {With a sharp game.}) 25... g6 {Winning back the piece with interest.} 26. Qc3 gxh5 {And Black is clearly better.}) 24. gxh4 Qxh4 25. Bxf7+ {Else the attack simply breaks through.} (25. Bg4 $2 Bxg4 26. hxg4 Qxg4+ 27. Kf1 Qh3+ 28. Ke2 Rad8 {Black has a very dangerous attack.}) 25... Kxf7 26. Qb3+ Kg6 {With the bishop pair and a continuous attack, although White is still in the game. The starting position is from the game Menezes, Christoph - Berkes, Ferenc, Hungary 2022.} *

